    "remarks": {
      "sha256": "27e8181f1e5647d41e6fff3aa3519ebb7aad2918788856c709691a2e4229ed9e",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "It is easy to prove that $F(n)\\geq 1-o(1)$. \n\nSee also [248], [679], and [890]"
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "9032de370046dabd4854d2f507d431d8e56de490ecb2c6930125428c5b272caf",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "If $\\omega(n)$ counts the number of distinct prime divisors of $n$ then let\\[F(n)=\\max_k \\omega(n+k)\\frac{\\log\\log k}{\\log k}.\\]Prove that $F(n)\\to \\infty$ as $n\\to \\infty$."
    }
  },
